Inheritance is a mechanism where a child class acquires the properties and behaviors of a parent class, promoting massive code reuse.
```python
class Employee:
    def __init__(self, name, salary):
        self.name = name
        self.salary = salary

class Manager(Employee):
    def __init__(self, name, salary, department):
        super().__init__(name, salary) # Call parent constructor
        self.department = department

m = Manager('Alice', 90000, 'IT')
print(m.name, m.department)
```
